    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Isaiah",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 3,
        "summary": "Judah and Jerusalem will be punished for their disobedience\u2014The Lord pleads for and judges His people\u2014The daughters of Zion are cursed and tormented for their worldliness\u2014Compare 2\u00a0Nephi 13.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "For, behold, the Lord, the Lord of hosts, doth take away from Jerusalem and from Judah the stay and the staff, the whole stay of bread, and the whole stay of water,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 13:1 (1\u201326).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lev. 26:32 (26\u201333).",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 71
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lam. 1:11.",
                        "start": 129,
                        "end": 134
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The mighty man, and the man of war, the judge, and the prophet, and the prudent, and the ancient,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0elder (also v.\u00a05).",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 865
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The captain of fifty, and the honourable man, and the counsellor, and the cunning artificer, and the eloquent orator.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0the wise man of magic arts.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 91
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0skillful enchanter.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 116
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will give children to be their princes, and babes shall rule over them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 10:16.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 30
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And the people shall be oppressed, every one by another, and every one by his neighbour: the child shall behave himself proudly against the ancient, and the base against the honourable.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 28:50 (49\u201351); Lam. 4:16 (16\u201317).",
                        "start": 140,
                        "end": 147
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When a man shall take hold of his brother of the house of his father, saying, Thou hast clothing, be thou our ruler, and let this ruin be under thy hand:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 13:6.",
                        "start": 130,
                        "end": 134
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 121,
                        "end": 124
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 135,
                        "end": 137
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "In that day shall he swear, saying, I will not be an healer; for in my house is neither bread nor clothing: make me not a ruler of the people.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0a binder up (of a wound); i.e., I cannot solve your problems.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 79
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For Jerusalem is ruined, and Judah is fallen: because their tongue and their doings are against the Lord, to provoke the eyes of his glory.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Micah 3:12.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lam. 1:3 (1\u20133).",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The shew of their countenance doth witness against them; and they declare their sin as Sodom, they hide it not. Woe unto their soul! for they have rewarded evil unto themselves.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 19:5. TG\u00a0Apostasy of Israel.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 83
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 13:10 (10\u201313); Deut. 32:32.",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Say ye to the righteous, that it shall be well with him: for they shall eat the fruit of their doings.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 8:12. TG\u00a0Righteousness.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 128:2.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Woe unto the wicked! it shall be ill with him: for the reward of his hands shall be given him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 11:6.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0the recompense of his deeds shall be done to him.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As for my people, children are their oppressors, and women rule over them. O my people, they which lead thee cause thee to err, and destroy the way of thy paths.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 3:16\u20134:1.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 58
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 1:13.",
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 119
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The Lord standeth up to plead, and standeth to judge the people.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0contend. Micah 6:2.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The Lord will enter into judgment with the ancients of his people, and the princes thereof: for ye have eaten up the vineyard; the spoil of the poor is in your houses.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Judge.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0elders.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0rulers or leaders.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 82
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0consumed or burned.",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 112
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0embezzled gain.",
                        "start": 131,
                        "end": 136
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 22:12 (6\u201313); Amos 3:10; Alma 4:12 (12\u201313).",
                        "start": 144,
                        "end": 148
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 149,
                        "end": 151
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "What mean ye that ye beat my people to pieces, and grind the faces of the poor? saith the Lord God of hosts.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Amos 2:6\u20137; 4:1; D&C 52:40.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Moreover the Lord saith, Because the daughters of Zion are haughty, and walk with stretched forth necks and wanton eyes, walking and mincing as they go, and making a tinkling with their feet:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Modesty.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 46
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Haughtiness; Vanity.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking in Darkness.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 76
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Carnal Mind.",
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 114
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0walking with short, rapid steps in an affected manner.",
                        "start": 133,
                        "end": 140
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 141,
                        "end": 143
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore the Lord will smite with a scab the crown of the head of the daughters of Zion, and the Lord will discover their secret parts.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0expose; idiom meaning \u201cput them to shame.\u201d",
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 135
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "In that day the Lord will take away the bravery of their tinkling ornaments about their feet, and their cauls, and their round tires like the moon,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Possibly hairnets. Authorities do not always agree on the nature of the female ornaments listed in vv.\u00a018\u201323.",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 109
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0ornaments shaped like a crescent moon.",
                        "start": 121,
                        "end": 126
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 93
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 103
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 120
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The chains, and the bracelets, and the mufflers,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0veils.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The bonnets, and the ornaments of the legs, and the headbands, and the tablets, and the earrings,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The rings, and nose jewels,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The changeable suits of apparel, and the mantles, and the wimples, and the crisping pins,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0resplendent garments.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apparel.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The glasses, and the fine linen, and the hoods, and the veils.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0transparent garments.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 11
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it shall come to pass, that instead of sweet smell there shall be stink; and instead of a girdle a rent; and instead of well set hair baldness; and instead of a stomacher a girding of sackcloth; and burning instead of beauty.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0rags.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 107
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 15:2; Ezek. 7:18 (18\u201319); Amos 8:10.",
                        "start": 138,
                        "end": 146
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0a robe.",
                        "start": 163,
                        "end": 174
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0branding (a mark of slavery).",
                        "start": 203,
                        "end": 210
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Beauty.",
                        "start": 222,
                        "end": 228
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 199,
                        "end": 202
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Thy men shall fall by the sword, and thy mighty in the war.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 4:1; Amos 4:10.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 7
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And her gates shall lament and mourn; and she being desolate shall sit upon the ground.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lam. 2:9 (8\u201310).",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lam. 2:8.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lam. 1:4 (4\u20136).",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0Jerusalem shall be emptied, cleaned out.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lam. 2:10.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}